---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 161
By: Sri Ramakrishna
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Renunciation-Detachment=Detachment and Serenity
  - 532
---
Unless the mind becomes steady there cannnot be yoga. It is the wind of
worldliness that always disturbs the mind, which may be likened to a
candle-flame. If that flame doesn't move at all. then one is said to have
attained yoga.
